  m_Name: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D3_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Proximal_Phalanx_D3_R
  partName: Pes Proximal Phalanx D3 Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right proximal phalanx of the third hind digit forms the first phalangeal
    segment connecting the metatarsal bone to the middle phalanx. This structure
    contributes to flexibility, balance, and coordinated toe movement during locomotion
    and weight-bearing activities.
  - Tendons and ligaments attached to the bone allow controlled flexion and extension
    necessary for stable hindpaw mechanics. The third digit assists significantly
    with traction and support during walking and running. Proper alignment and structural
    integrity of the proximal phalanx are essential for efficient movement.
